<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-06-24T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-06-24T14:00:00-05:00" n="168" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d168">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">825.6374/1173a: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Culbertson</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-06-24T15:00:00-04:00">June 24, 1933—3
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>33. Please send by first air mail latest available text of bill for
                            reorganizing nitrate industry. Communication just received from one of
                            the interests represented refers to “seventh and definitive draft” of
                            which Department has no copy. Keep Department currently advised by air
                            mail of any changes in text.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>